1. cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) - The paper proposes a new indexing technique for point-to-point distance querying, which is a fundamental problem in data structures and algorithms. 
2. cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) - The paper focuses on scale-free graphs, which are commonly used to model social and information networks. 
3. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The paper discusses computation costs and I/O costs, which are important considerations in designing efficient systems. 
4. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper deals with distance querying, which is a common problem in networking and internet architecture. 
5. cs.CE (Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science) - The paper proposes a new technique for handling massive graphs, which is relevant to computational engineering, finance, and science applications.
